title: Grateful Dead Live at Recreation Hall, UC Davis on 1982-03-14
lineage: Dat Sony PCM-R500 > Tascam DA-3000 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/44.1k  1 DVD FLAC Transfer By Charlie Miller
description:
Set I
One More Saturday Night-> Sugaree, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Bird Song-> Little Red Rooster, Ramble On Rose-> Looks Like Rain, Althea, Let It Grow
Set II
Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Playin' In The Band-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Phil Birthday space During space around the 2 minute mark you can hear them playing happy birthday. Although a day early I would think this is for Phil. seeing as his B day is 3 15 1940.
Having listened to the sound board of this show only a handful of times maybe 5 or 6 times I never picked up it before till the clearer board came out yesterday.  
This board isn't best but it is the complete show . Not much jam too it though, play list in 2nd set looks real good on paper but they just don't go crazy with it . 
The aud version of this one is better to me. We had a copy along time ago and played that many many times.
